This isn‚Äôt Disney Mario Kart! It‚Äôs a simple Disneyfied racer with some strategy elements! It‚Äôs cute and fun but no Forza!  If this might be up your alley read my review further‚Ä¶ 

Regarding the negative reviewers who are rating down because of the F2P model. It was always going to be Free to play after paid Early Access. We are paying to help shape the game from this point. If you wanna help offer feedback and offer suggestions to make this game better in quality and content, then jump on board during Early Access. 

Eventually this will have a monetization aspect with micro transactions. That‚Äôs what free to play is. If you don‚Äôt agree with that business, games as a service model then I recommend you pass on this. 

Anyways; 

Pros; 
Beautiful  visuals, booming tracks, loving the starting character roster! Loving the variety of modes. Game runs great on Steam deck. I have it running at 60 FPS during races. It drops to about 15-30 during loading and sits at 25-40 idling in menus. 

Battery goes from 100% to 75% in one hour on steam deck with 85% volume and max brightness. Then drops to 50% an hour and a half in. 

Modes right now I‚Äôve tried; 
Ranked Multiplayer, Regulated Multiplayer, Season Challenges with a theme, single player mode with challenges, weekly and daily challenges, offline local player mode I have played with the hubby. 

This game wasn‚Äôt hard to learn or grasp. Lots of modes that offer challenge but not aggravating. I‚Äôm sure multiplayer will get super competitive as time goes on. 

Cons; 
