What happens when you take a platformer, base building, stealth, rouguelike and add cute 8 bit gameplay?

You get possibly one of the best games ever made, Mr. Sun's Hatbox. Holy hell guys I am not joking when I say that this quite literally combines all my favorite parts of niche indie games and meshes it into a big fun mess. If you were here for the review & wanted to know whether or not you should get it? It's a definite MUST and in my honest opinion a strong contender for MY Game of the Year. But if you want to know why, keep watching.



//graphics, sound & artstyle//

While the 8 Bit style of yesteryear has worn its welcome, Mr Sun's Hatbox is elevated by it. Accompanied by the wonderful sfx of the entire world & the music, it's simply spectacular. As a sidenote, a lot of the little helpers you get have quirks- some of them may be deaf or hard of hearing, the way the game changes while you're controlling them, whether muffled sounds or no sound at all deserves some recognition


//Gameplay//

You are part of the most elite delivery service in the world, so DEFINITELY not FedEx.. and while delivering a hat to Mr. Sun, some ruffians steal the package. It's up to you to intercept that package right back (as he did have insurance on that). You start by setting up a base of operations, a mission control panel, staff room, storage, medbay and brig to... brainwash people you kidnap into joining your cause... Missions are scanned in the world, and their difficulty level and what you will be doing for example, killing a target, kidnapping them, surviving a raid, delivering a package, stealing a package, etc etc. You send a worker to a mission PERMADEATH IS ALWAYS ON (can be switched off but so will achievements be in the menu) so be careful, you are given balloons that will send gear, hats & enemies back to your base, upon completing missions your workers will gain exp and the reward advertised. With leveling up, your worker CAN lose bad quirks.

The ultimate objective is to get Mr. Sun's hat back by any means necessary, that will mean later on, opening up a black market, building research facilities, building facilities among other great helps. Eventually you will even be able to build a lab that can add and take quirks away!




//Price//

14.99 USD




//How Many Hours Estimated//

Alright, I'm about 3/5 done with the story (what I believe) and i'm 8 hours in. Doing it completely single player BUT also, once I'm done- my partner & myself are going in it HARD cause it's got co-op. I'm estimating I'm gonna do at least 50 hours.


//Is it SteamDeck Playable?//

Yep! It is, although the control of guns feel a little weird, I still COULD play it just as I can on my computer.


//Final Thoughts//



This is THE Indie Game. So much brutality and such cuteness all combined so perfectly. Mr. Sun's Hatbox as aforementioned is a game that I feel could be my Game of the Year, I've been having so much fun just going into missions and getting money to upgrade my facilities, brainwashing guys I think could be useful and even came up with this cool little exploit where I buy whatever the Black Market has for 50% off and then sell it at my store for full price. It seemed really easy at first but BOY was I wrong, I kept getting my a** kicked and at one point I didn't even notice but it was the same guy molly whooping me. Ole Shade Bray, his little b* a**, taking two of my guys- I was finally gonna be able to exact revenge on him.. sending my Gunbye Steele into battle and offing him was TOO satisfying. However, later on Gunbye Steele was kidnapped and when I did a mission to retrieve him, I accidentally blew him up while fighting to get him out... Nemesis System is something I did not expect to have while playing this, but man has it made such a resounding impact on my current gameplay. I'm having so much fun with this and I since the beginning like I said, just go ahead and buy it. Guns, hats, cute little psychopaths, this game has it all. 

I didn't even mention that you could rename them but I feel like every time I did, it was like putting the dagger in their last little heart. 

And as far as complaints go? I really have none. Each hat has it's own purpose, even if some don't you'll be using them for research later or contracts on the black market. It's fast, and rewarding and most of all a ton of fun. i can't wait to dive back into it and get lost for another few hours. 


[h1] Buy it Now! [/h1]
